==English==

==Noun==

covert-coat

# A covert-coat is a coat suitable for wearing while shooting game (eg with a neutral colour and windproof or waterproof qualities). 

==Usage examples==

Hornung: Raffles: 1899 (p 10 of 1994 edition): Meanwhile Raffles rejoined me, with a covert-coat over his blazer, and a soft felt hat set carelessly on the curly head he shook with a smile as I passed him the decanter.